    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Round, broad-brimmed ecclesiastical hats with low crowns made of felt or beaver hair. Prelatial hats are black, except those worn by the pope or cardinals. A silk band or cord with tassels encircles the crown, with the color indicative of the wearer's rank.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
